Personal Finance Expense Tracker – Console Based Project:
===========================================================


1: Expense Class
	Fields:
		• int id
		• double amount
		• String category
		• LocalDate date
		• String note
- Add constructors, getters, setters, and toString ().
---------------------------------------------------------

2: ExpenseManager Class

Handles all business operations.
	Data Structures Used:
		• ArrayList<Expense> expenses → stores all expenses
		• PriorityQueue<Expense> maxPQ → highest expense first
		• PriorityQueue<Expense> minPQ → lowest expense first
Functions inside ExpenseManager:
	1. addExpense(Expense e)
	2. viewAllExpenses()
	3. viewByCategory(String category)
	4. viewByMonth(int month, int year)
	5. getTotalExpense()
	6. getHighestExpense() → uses max PriorityQueue
	7. getLowestExpense() → uses min PriorityQueue

-----------------------------------------------------------
3. Detailed Description of Each Feature

a . Add Expense
User enters:
	• Amount
	• Category (Food, Travel, Shopping, etc.)
	• Date (YYYY-MM-DD)
	• Note
System:
	• Creates an Expense object
	• Adds it to ArrayList
	• Adds it to maxPQ and minPQ
________________________________________
b . View All Expenses
	Simply loop through ArrayList<Expense> and print.
________________________________________
c . View Expenses by Category
	• Get category from user
	• Loop and display matching entries
	• Comparison should be case-insensitive
________________________________________
d . Monthly Summary
Input: month + year
The system displays:
	• All expenses of that month
	• Total spent
	• Number of expenses
	• Highest expense of that month
	• Lowest expense of that month
(Use filtering + temporary variables)
________________________________________
e . Get Total Expense
	Traverse the ArrayList → sum all amounts.
________________________________________
f . Highest Expense (Using PriorityQueue)
	maxPQ - peek() returns the highest amount expense instantly.
________________________________________
g . Lowest Expense (Using PriorityQueue)
	minPQ- peek() returns the lowest amount expense instantly.
	
------------------------------------------------------------

4. Build Full Menu-Driven Application

- Implement all features in one console application.
- Include add, view, filter, monthly summary, highest/lowest, and exit.
- Ensure input validation.
